ore November 1220","1145–1220":"1145–1220","1155–1222":"1155–1222","1170–1287":"1170–1287","1124–Male":"1124–Deceased","about 1170":"about 1170","before 1200":"before 1200","1220":"1220","1170":"1170","1215":"1215","1124":"1124","1222":"1222","1145":"1145","1287":"1287","1155":"1155","about 1145":"about 1145","before November 1220":"before November 1220","about 1098":"about 1098","Bracewell, Yorkshire, England":"Bracewell, Yorkshire, England","Bracewell, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bracewell, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Tempest","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Yorkshire): nickname for someone with a blustery temperament, from Middle English, Old French <i>tempest(e)</i> ‘storm’ (from Latin <i>tempestas</i> ‘weather, season’, a derivative of <i>tempus</i> ‘time’)."],"variants":[{"name":"Tempesta","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Antonio, Carlo, Raffaele, Agostino, Angelo, Carmelo, Cesare, Cesidio, Dante, Elio, Ezio, Gino.","Italian: nickname for someone with a stormy temperament, from <i>tempesta</i> ‘storm, tempest’ (see   Tempest  )."]}]},{"name":"Roger","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French personal name, <i>Rog(i)er</i>, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, from <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>gār</i>, <i>gēr</i> ‘spear’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain, replacing the native Old English form <i>Hrōðgār</i>. <i>Roger</i> was one of the most popular boys' names throughout the medieval period, but less so after the Reformation, though it has continued in regular use to the present day.  Roger, Count of Sicily  (  <i>c.</i>1031–1101 ), son of Tancred, recovered Sicily from the Arabs. His son, also called Roger, ruled Sicily as king, presiding over a court noted for its splendour and patronage of the arts."],"variants":[{"name":"Rodger","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Roger  , in part from the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":70,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Roger Tempest I was born about 1145, in Bracewell, Yorkshire, England as the son of Richard I Tempest. He married Lady Alice Rilleston before 1200. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died before November 1220, in his hometown."},"et":{"about 1145–before November 1220":"umbes 1145–enne novembrit 1220","1145–1220":"1145–1220","1155–1222":"1155–1222","1170–1287":"1170–1287","1124–Male":"1124–Surnud","about 1170":"umbes 1170","before 1200":"enne 1200","1220":"1220","1170":"1170","1215":"1215","1124":"1124","1222":"1222","1145":"1145","1287":"1287","1155":"1155","about 1145":"umbes 1145","before November 1220":"enne novembrit 1220","about 1098":"about 1098","Bracewell, Yorkshire, England":"Bracewell, Yorkshire, England","Bracewell, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bracewell, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1145–before November 1220":"noin 1145–ennen vuotta marraskuu 1220","1145–1220":"1145–1220","1155–1222":"1155–1222","1170–1287":"1170–1287","1124–Male":"1124–Kuollut","about 1170":"noin 1170","before 1200":"ennen vuotta 1200","1220":"1220","1170":"1170","1215":"1215","1124":"1124","1222":"1222","1145":"1145","1287":"1287","1155":"1155","about 1145":"noin 1145","before November 1220":"ennen